'''BabelNet'''是一个[[多語言|多语]]词汇[[语义网络_(计算机科学)|语义网络]]和[[本体_(信息科学)|本体]]，由[[罗马大学|罗马萨皮恩扎大学]]（罗马大学）计算机科学系的计算语言学实验室所创建。<ref name="NavigliPonzetto12">R. Navigli and S. P Ponzetto. 2012. [[doi:10.1016/j.artint.2012.07.001|BabelNet: The Automatic Construction, Evaluation and Application of a Wide-Coverage Multilingual Semantic Network]]. Artificial Intelligence, 193, Elsevier, pp. 217-250.</ref><ref>R. Navigli, S. P. Ponzetto. [http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/P/P10/P10-1023.pdf BabelNet: Building a Very Large Multilingual Semantic Network] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/P/P10/P10-1023.pdf |date=20160729231510 }}. Proc. of the 48th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics (ACL 2010), Uppsala, Sweden, July 11–16, 2010, pp. 216–225.</ref> BabelNet是自动构建的，其将最大的多语Web[[百科全书|百科全书]][[维基百科|维基百科]]链接到最常用的[[英语|英语]]计算词典[[WordNet|WordNet]]。这种链接整合，以自动映射的方式完成；对于资源匮乏的[[语言|语言]]所存在的词汇空缺，借助于[[统计机器翻译|统计机器翻译]]来补充。其结果是一个“百科词典”，提供了多种语言的[[概念|概念]]和{{tsl|en|Named_entity|命名实体}}，并包含了它们之间的丰富的语义关系。通过与免费授权使用的{{tsl|en|OmegaWiki|OmegaWiki}}、英语[[维基词典|维基词典]]、[[维基数据|维基数据]]、{{tsl|en|FrameNet|FrameNet}}、{{tsl|en|VerbNet|VerbNet}}等语义资源建立链接，BabelNet还补充了其它一些词汇和定义。和WordNet类似，BabelNet将不同语言中的词语以[[同义词|同义词]]集的形式进行组织，称之为Babel synset。对于每一个Babel {{tsl|en|Synonym_ring|synset}}，BabelNet提供简短的定义（称为[[注释|注释]]），这些定义具有多种语言版本，主要来自于WordNet和维基百科。

== BabelNet的数据统计 ==
截至2016年8月，BabelNet（v3.7）已覆盖了271种[[语言|语言]]，包栝全部的[[欧洲语言|欧洲语言]]、大多数[[亚洲|亚洲]]语言及[[拉丁语|拉丁语]]。BabelNet 3.7包含了大约1400万个同义词集和7.46亿个[[词义|词义]]（不论其语言）。在每种语言中，每个Babel synset（词义）平均包含2个同义词。BabelNet的语义网络包含了丰富的词汇语义关系。这些语义关系有两个来源：一是，来自于WordNet的语义关系，如[[上下位关系|上下位关系]]、部分整体关系、[[反义词|反义]]、[[同义词|同义关系]]等，总共大约36.4万条关系；二是，来自于维基百科的非特定的相关关系，总共大约3.8亿条关系。<ref name="NavigliPonzetto12" /> BabelNet 3.7将大约1100万张图片与Babel synset建立了关联，并为这些资源提供了Lemon [[RDF|RDF]]编码<ref>M. Ehrmann, F. Cecconi, D. Vannella, J. McCrae, P. Cimiano, R. Navigli. [http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/810_Paper.pdf Representing Multilingual Data as Linked Data: the Case of BabelNet 2.0] {{Wayback|url=http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/810_Paper.pdf |date=20160304195701 }}. Proc. of the 9th Language Resources and Evaluation Conference (LREC 2014), Reykjavik, Iceland, 26–31 May 2014.</ref>，可通过[[SPARQL|SPARQL]] endpoint获取。BabelNet 3.7为267万个同义词集指定了领域标签。

== 应用 ==
BabelNet可广泛应用在多语[[自然语言处理|自然语言处理]]中。BabelNet中的词汇化知识可在以下任务中取得最佳效果：
* {{tsl|en|Semantic_similarity|语义相关性}}<ref>R. Navigli and S. Ponzetto. 2012. [http://www.aaai.org/ocs/index.php/AAAI/AAAI12/paper/download/5112/5126 BabelRelate! A Joint Multilingual Approach to Computing Semantic Relatedness] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aaai.org/ocs/index.php/AAAI/AAAI12/paper/download/5112/5126 |date=20160303230903 }}. Proc. of the 26th AAAI Conference on Artificial Intelligence (AAAI 2012), Toronto, Canada, pp. 108-114.</ref><ref>J. Camacho-Collados, M. T. Pilehvar and R. Navigli. [http://aclweb.org/anthology/N/N15/N15-1059.pdf NASARI: a Novel Approach to a Semantically-Aware Representation of Items] {{Wayback|url=http://aclweb.org/anthology/N/N15/N15-1059.pdf |date=20160430035413 }}. Proc. of the 2015 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (NAACL 2015), Denver, Colorado (US), 31 May-5 June 2015, pp. 567-577.</ref>
* 多语[[词义消歧|词义消歧]]<ref>R. Navigli and S. Ponzetto. [http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/D12-1128 Joining Forces Pays Off: Multilingual Joint Word Sense Disambiguation] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/D12-1128 |date=20160303180416 }}. Proc. of the 2012 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing (EMNLP 2012), Jeju, Korea, July 12–14, 2012, pp. 1399-1410.</ref>
* 基于Babelfy系统的多语词义消岐及{{tsl|en|Entity_linking|实体链接}}<ref>A. Moro, A. Raganato, R. Navigli. [http://www.transacl.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/54.pdf Entity Linking meets Word Sense Disambiguation: a Unified Approach] {{Wayback|url=http://www.transacl.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/54.pdf |date=20140808063116 }}. Transactions of the Association for Computational Linguistics (TACL), 2, pp. 231-244, 2014.</ref>
* {{tsl|en|Human-based_computation_game|有目的的视频游戏}}<ref>D. Jurgens, R. Navigli. [http://www.transacl.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/421-camera-ready.pdf It's All Fun and Games until Someone Annotates: Video Games with a Purpose for Linguistic Annotation] {{Wayback|url=http://www.transacl.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/421-camera-ready.pdf |date=20150103085712 }}. Transactions of the Association for Computational Linguistics (TACL), 2, pp. 449-464, 2014.</ref>
